====================================================================================================
5-STEP ASCII ROADMAP TO LEARN JAVA OOPS 
====================================================================================================
RULES
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) CODE DAILY (EVEN 45 MIN) — OOPS IS NOT THEORY-ONLY
2) AFTER EVERY TOPIC, BUILD A TINY PROGRAM (5–15 MIN)
3) ONE NOTEBOOK: "WHAT IT IS" + "WHY" + "WHEN TO USE" + "COMMON MISTAKE"
4) DO NOT JUMP TO INTERFACES/ABSTRACTION BEFORE ENCAPSULATION + INHERITANCE BASICS
5) EVERY WEEK: 1 MINI-PROJECT ONLY USING WHAT YOU LEARNED

====================================================================================================
PHASE 1/5 — OOPS FOUNDATION MINDSET DAYS (1-3)
====================================================================================================
GOAL: UNDERSTAND WHY OOPS EXISTS + THINK IN OBJECTS

[LEARN]
  • (1) WHY OOPS EXISTS (PROCEDURAL LIMITATIONS, REUSABILITY, MAINTAINABILITY)
  • REAL-WORLD MODELING: OBJECT = THING, CLASS = BLUEPRINT

[DO]
  • WRITE 3 REAL-WORLD MODELS (NO CODING FIRST):
      1) STUDENT (ID, NAME, BRANCH) + BEHAVIORS (DISPLAY, UPDATE)
      2) BANK ACCOUNT (BALANCE) + BEHAVIORS (DEPOSIT, WITHDRAW)
      3) MUSIC PLAYER SONG (TITLE, ARTIST) + BEHAVIOR (PLAY, STOP)

[CODE PRACTICE]
  • CREATE 1 SIMPLE CLASS PER MODEL
  • CREATE 3 OBJECTS AND PRINT THEIR STATE

[CHECKPOINT]
  • YOU CAN EXPLAIN: "WHY OOPS?" IN 5 LINES + GIVE 2 REAL EXAMPLES


====================================================================================================
PHASE 2/5 — CLASS, OBJECT, CONSTRUCTORS, THIS (DAYS 4–10)
====================================================================================================
GOAL: BUILD OBJECTS CORRECTLY + STOP BEGINNER BUGS

[LEARN]
  • (2) CLASS & OBJECT
  • (3) CONSTRUCTORS (DEFAULT, PARAMETERIZED, OVERLOADING)
  • (4) THIS KEYWORD (CURRENT OBJECT, CONSTRUCTOR CHAINING this())

[DO MINI PROGRAMS]
  • STUDENT:
      - DEFAULT CONSTRUCTOR
      - PARAMETERIZED CONSTRUCTOR
      - DISPLAY METHOD
  • RECTANGLE:
      - LENGTH, BREADTH
      - AREA(), PERIMETER()
  • EMPLOYEE:
      - this USED TO RESOLVE NAME CONFLICT
      - this() CHAINING (CALL ONE CONSTRUCTOR FROM ANOTHER)

[COMMON BUGS TO KILL]
  • FORGETTING TO INITIALIZE FIELDS
  • CONFUSING CONSTRUCTOR WITH METHOD
  • USING local VARIABLE INSTEAD OF instance VARIABLE (FIX WITH this)

[CHECKPOINT]
  • YOU CAN WRITE A CLASS WITH 2 CONSTRUCTORS + this() CHAINING WITHOUT HELP


====================================================================================================
PHASE 3/5 — ENCAPSULATION + ACCESS + STATIC + FINAL (DAYS 11–18)
====================================================================================================
GOAL: WRITE SAFE CLASSES LIKE REAL JAVA PROJECTS

[LEARN]
  • (5) ENCAPSULATION (PRIVATE FIELDS + GET/SET + VALIDATION)
  • (10) ACCESS MODIFIERS (PUBLIC/PRIVATE/PROTECTED/DEFAULT)
  • (11) STATIC (CLASS LEVEL)
  • (12) FINAL (CONSTANTS, NO OVERRIDE, NO INHERIT)

[DO MINI PROGRAMS]
  • BANK ACCOUNT (BEST FOR ENCAPSULATION):
      - private balance
      - deposit(amount) VALIDATION
      - withdraw(amount) VALIDATION
      - getBalance() (READ-ONLY STYLE)
  • CONFIG CLASS:
      - public static final TAX_RATE
      - final class Utility (NO INHERIT)
  • COUNTER:
      - static COUNT INCREASES WHEN OBJECTS CREATED

[CHECKPOINT]
  • YOU CAN EXPLAIN: "WHY PRIVATE?" + "WHY GETTERS/SETTERS?" + "WHEN STATIC?"


====================================================================================================
PHASE 4/5 — INHERITANCE + POLYMORPHISM (DAYS 19–28)
====================================================================================================
GOAL: IS-A CLEAR + OVERRIDING + DYNAMIC DISPATCH

[LEARN]
  • (6) INHERITANCE (extends, super, constructor chain)
  • (7) POLYMORPHISM
      - OVERLOADING (COMPILE TIME)
      - OVERRIDING (RUNTIME)
      - UPCASTING + BASIC DOWNCASTING

[DO MINI PROGRAMS]
  • PERSON -> STUDENT -> RESEARCH STUDENT (MULTILEVEL)
  • VEHICLE -> BUS, TRUCK (HIERARCHICAL)
  • SHAPE -> CIRCLE, RECTANGLE (OVERRIDE area())

[PRACTICE MUST-DO]
  • SUPER() CALL ORDER PRINT STATEMENTS
  • PARENT REF = CHILD OBJ:
      Vehicle v = new Bus();
      v.start();  // CHILD METHOD RUNS (DYNAMIC DISPATCH)

[WHEN TO AVOID INHERITANCE]
  • IF RELATIONSHIP IS "HAS-A" (USE COMPOSITION)

[CHECKPOINT]
  • YOU CAN PREDICT OUTPUT OF OVERRIDING + CONSTRUCTOR CHAIN QUESTIONS


====================================================================================================
PHASE 5/5 — ABSTRACTION + INTERFACES + OBJECT CLASS + MEMORY + EXCEPTIONS + DESIGN (DAYS 29–45)
====================================================================================================
GOAL: LEVEL UP FROM CODER TO DESIGNER

[LEARN]
  • (8) ABSTRACTION (ABSTRACT CLASS/METHODS)
  • (9) INTERFACES (IMPLEMENTS, MULTIPLE INHERITANCE VIA INTERFACES)
  • (13) OBJECT CLASS (toString, equals, hashCode)
  • (14) MEMORY (HEAP, REFERENCES, GC BASICS)
  • (15) EXCEPTIONS (TRY/CATCH, THROW/THROWS, CUSTOM)
  • (16) DESIGN PRACTICES (LOOSE COUPLING, HIGH COHESION)

[DO MINI PROGRAMS]
  • PAYMENT SYSTEM:
      interface Payment { pay(amount); }
      class UpiPayment, CardPayment implements Payment
  • ABSTRACT EMPLOYEE:
      abstract class Employee { abstract double salary(); }
      FULLTIME, INTERN extends Employee
  • OBJECT METHODS:
      - OVERRIDE toString() FOR CLEAN PRINT
      - OVERRIDE equals() + hashCode() FOR ID-BASED COMPARISON
  • CUSTOM EXCEPTION:
      - InsufficientBalanceException

[CHECKPOINT]
  • YOU CAN DESIGN A SMALL SYSTEM USING INTERFACE + ABSTRACT CLASS CORRECTLY


====================================================================================================
WEEKLY MINI-PROJECTS (VERY IMPORTANT)
====================================================================================================
WEEK 1: STUDENT MANAGEMENT (ADD, DISPLAY, UPDATE) USING CLASS/CONSTRUCTOR/THIS
WEEK 2: BANK ACCOUNT SYSTEM USING ENCAPSULATION + VALIDATION
WEEK 3: TRANSPORT SYSTEM USING INHERITANCE + POLYMORPHISM
WEEK 4: PAYMENT / NOTIFICATION SYSTEM USING INTERFACES + ABSTRACTION + EXCEPTIONS

====================================================================================================
DAILY STUDY TEMPLATE (SIMPLE BUT POWERFUL)
====================================================================================================
1) 20 MIN THEORY (WHY + RULES)
2) 40 MIN CODING (1 CLASS + 1 TEST IN MAIN)
3) 20 MIN QUESTIONS (OUTPUT PREDICTION + "WHY" QUESTIONS)
4) 10 MIN NOTES (COMMON MISTAKES + KEY RULES)
====================================================================================================
